8.4.2

Firt, the boost algorithm calculates the model step by step, where = 0 and r_i = y_i for all values of i. The algorithim then iterate over each value of i for each step. This results in a calculation of 1/lambda * f_i(xi) for every value of i. Then another stump i fit to maximize the fit to residuals.

So, = lambda + lambda and r_i = y_i - lambda - lambda for all values of i. This results in the model of the form suggested at the beginning of the problem.

8.4.3

p <- seq(0, 1, 0.01)
gini_index <- 2 * p * (1-p)
class_error <- 1 - pmax(p, 1 - p)
class_entropy <- - ((p * log(p)) + (1 - p) * log(1-p))
matplot(p, cbind(gini_index, class_error, class_entropy), col = c("red", "orange", "green"))

table(Weekly_test$Direction)
